# Landing Design Consistency

Use the existing landing visual system; do not introduce a new style direction.

- Use only tokens from `apps/landing/app/globals.css` (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-card`), and avoid hardcoded hex colors unless matching an existing token.
- Keep typography consistent: Arabic-first copy, `dir="rtl"` layouts, `font-sans` for body/headings, and `font-mono`/JetBrains Mono only for numbers, money, codes, or IDs.
- Preserve the section rhythm: container `max-w-7xl`, horizontal padding `px-4 lg:px-8`, vertical spacing around `py-16 lg:py-24`, and alternating `bg-card` / `bg-secondary` sections.
- Reuse established component shapes: `rounded-lg` or `rounded-xl`, subtle borders (`border-border`), and light shadows (`shadow-[0_1px_3px_rgba(0,0,0,0.08)]` / `shadow-sm`) instead of heavy effects.
- Keep CTA styling aligned with current patterns: primary CTA uses `bg-primary` + `text-primary-foreground` + `hover:bg-primary-hover`; secondary CTA uses border-primary outline style.
- For forms, maintain current control language: minimum `h-12`, outlined inputs (`border-[1.5px] border-input`), clear focus ring using `ring-ring`, and concise inline validation text.
- Match current motion style: Framer Motion fade/slide with small offsets (`~20-30px`) and durations around `0.4-0.7s`; avoid dramatic/long animations.
- Prefer existing UI primitives in `components/ui` (`Button`, `Input`, `Label`, etc.) and existing section patterns before creating new one-off styles.
- Treat `apps/landing/styles/globals.css` as legacy; keep the active source of truth in `apps/landing/app/globals.css`.
